# 📊 Unemployment Analysis (Covid-19 Impact in India)

## 📌 Objective

The objective of this project is to analyze the unemployment rate in India and understand the impact of the Covid-19 pandemic using data analysis and visualization techniques.

## 🛠 Tools & Technologies

* Python
* Pandas
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn
* Jupyter Notebook

## 📊 Project Description

In this project, unemployment data is analyzed to identify trends and patterns over time. The focus is on understanding how the Covid-19 pandemic affected unemployment rates in India. Data cleaning techniques were applied to handle missing values, duplicates, and incorrect data types.

## 📈 Analysis

* Filtered India-specific data
* Focused on Covid period (2020–2021)
* Visualized unemployment trends using line graphs
* Highlighted the Covid impact period

## 🧹 Data Cleaning

* Removed null values
* Removed duplicate records
* Converted data types
* Handled invalid values

## 🎯 Conclusion

The analysis shows that unemployment rates increased during the Covid-19 period due to economic slowdown and job losses. A gradual recovery can be observed after the pandemic.

